The genetic disorders associated with cancer often result from an alteration or mutation in a single gene.  The diseases range from rare dominant cancer family syndrome to familial tendencies in which low-penetrance genes may interact with other genes or environmental factors to induce cancer.  Research may involve clinical, epidemiologic, and laboratory studies of persons, families, and populations at high risk of these disorders._A disease characterized by chronic hemolytic anemia, episodic painful crises, and pathologic involvement of many organs. Concepts.definition: Transmitted through genes from parents to offspring. (genome.gov)

Genetic diseases are diseases in which inherited genes predispose to increased risk. The genetic disorders associated with cancer often result from an alteration or mutation in a single gene. The diseases range from rare dominant cancer family syndrome to familial tendencies in which low-penetrance genes may interact with other genes or environmental factors to induce cancer. Research may involve clinical, epidemiologic, and laboratory studies of persons, families, and populations at high risk of these disorders.

Property.preferredDefinition: A disease characterized by chronic hemolytic anemia, episodic painful crises, and pathologic involvement of many organs. It is the clinical expression of homozygosity for hemoglobin S.

Concepts.definition: A blood disorder characterized by the appearance of sickle-shaped red blood cells and anemia.
